    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>Let <m>U</m> be a matrix whose columns are orthonormal. Let <m>P = UU^T</m> . Show that <m>\Col(P) = \Col(U)</m>. Use the identity <m>P^2 = P</m> to show that the eigenvalues of <m>P</m> equal <m>0</m> or <m>1</m>.</p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
